subSubSection.paragraph:
Teeth on jaws, vomer and palatines. Jaw teeth slightly recurved, blunt. Upper jaw with 5–17 large teeth in outer row (average 10.7 in
79 specimens
), 0–4 ( 0.4 ) in inner row, anterior teeth of outer row largest. Dentary with 5–17 ( 10.8 ) teeth in long inner row, 1–12 ( 6.1 ) in short outer row [sometimes up to 6 ( 0.6 ) teeth in intermediate row]. External and internal rows usually separated by space equal to external row width. Teeth of external row oriented outward and downward in horizontal plane. Vomer with an irregular patch of 1–5 ( 1.2 ) teeth (one specimen from Sea of Okhotsk (NSMT-P 67503 ) lacking vomerine teeth). Palatine with 2–8 ( 4.2 ) conical teeth in a single very short row.

Pectoral fin small, its length about half of head length, without notch, consisting of 14–17 (usually 15–16 ) branched rays, membranes of lower 4–5 rays weakly incised. Pelvic fin base usually posterior to isthmus. Pelvic fin long, its length about 60–70 % of eye diameter, slightly pointed posteriorly, not reaching pectoral fin base, consisting of 1 unsegmented outer ray and 2 segmented rays with innermost ray longest and branched (
Fig. 7
).

